The paper deals with the problem of multimodal information retrieval, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of deep learning and embeddings suggests that the paper could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). The focus on image-text relations and image captioning suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of metrics and experimental results suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, and cs.LG, in that order.
